column305:
The place offers a picturesque 360 degree panoramic view of the entire Ranchi from top. The Sunset is beautiful to watch.  One can easily spend an hour enjoying the beauty of Ranchi.

There are number of steps to the top which might be difficult for small kids and aged to climb. Carry drinking water with you as nothing is available right from entrance to the top.

The steps are broken at places, the place is I'll maintained, lacks cleanliness and is dirty. The murals on wall made of cement,  if maintained properly can be made attractive.

The garden requires upkeep.

Good drinking water and toilet is very much required.

After one gets down there are small shops which offers cool drinks, snacks and juices

Do I want to go again? - Definitely

column328:
The exhibit that I viewed at the Ranchi Museum of Art was one about Tribe Art between the years 1100-1500. This was a series of paintings, sculptures, architecture, and tapestry of the Medieval and Early Renaissance as well as objects from the Middle East. This exhibit was an important part of the history of the Jharkhand Tribe Museum of Art. It gave me a good idea of what the paintings were like in these four centuries and reflected ideas of both the east and the  our old cultures .
I also observed many paintings in this gallery. One painting that caught my eye was titled, ‚ÄúThe Mocking of labours ‚Äù. It was an early 11th century, oil on wood painting. Workers and Tribe was seen in the upper right next to families and was surrounded by figured who looked more like friends than enemies that would crucify him. These so called tribes of our old era that were holding weapons and wearing bizarre headgear. In many paintings, Tribes had a saddened look on his face while the others looked peculiar . I was attracted to this painting because I would never have thought that paintings have this much of details that i could ever get.

However, consuming any food items from the street side stalls like noodles, chaat, etc is a very big no-no, because they hardly sell and you can very much expect them to be stale and rotten.

column328: Best dam I have ever seen. The blue water and small green islands in between will give a pleasing perceptual experience to your senses. We arrived there at about 4 pm. The sun was about to set. Chords of soft light speared down from above, bathing its surface in gold. The best thing here is boating. There is speed boat available as well. But if you want to experience the beauty of the nature and each and every wave, then ride a man powered boat (without motor). The waves are so strong and high even when the dam has stopped the river water. There are two islands where you can go. The water is crystal clear here.
